{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3e7b2c1-9f4d-4a1e-b2c3-d4e5f6789012",
    "name": "Web API — Full roundtrip (auth + REST)",
    "description": "python-graphql-api web flow for admin-style REST.\n\n**Run with Collection Runner in order** (top to bottom).\n\n**Variables** (collection → Variables):\n- `baseUrl` — e.g. `http://localhost:5002`\n- `registerEmail`, `registerPassword` — web auth (min 8 chars)\n\n**Auto-set by tests:** `accessToken`, `customerId`, `addressId`, `addressId2`, `orderId`, `technicianId`\n\n**Addresses:** Steps **6A–6C** cover `POST/PUT /api/addresses` batch APIs and single-row `PUT /api/addresses/{id}`.\n\n**Notes:**\n- Register may return **409** if the email exists; run **Login** anyway.\n- **Deletes:** order **12** before customer **13** (FK on `bookings.customer_id`).\n- Ensure `users.internal_notes` exists if create/update customer uses notes (`scripts/add_users_internal_notes.sql`).\n- If `POST /api/technicians` fails with duplicate `technician_id`, fix the Postgres sequence on `technician_profiles`.\n- REST routes are open in code; Bearer is sent for parity with a secured gateway.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5002" },
    { "key": "registerEmail", "value": "web.postman.roundtrip@example.test" },
    { "key": "registerPassword", "value": "PostmanTest!8" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "customerId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "addressId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "addressId2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "orderId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "technicianId", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Register",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 Created or 409 exists', function () {",
              "  pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});",
              "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
              "  var j = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (j && j.accessToken) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
              "  }",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{registerEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{registerPassword}}\",\n  \"firstName\": \"Postman\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Web\",\n  \"role\": \"customer\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register",
        "description": "POST /api/auth/register — creates `users` row with password hash; may return token on 201."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Login",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.expect(j.accessToken, 'accessToken').to.be.ok;",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{registerEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{registerPassword}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
        "description": "POST /api/auth/login — stores JWT in collection variable `accessToken`."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Get technician list",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.expect(j).to.have.property('data');"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/technicians?page=1&limit=10",
        "description": "GET /api/technicians"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Get customer list",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/customers?page=1&limit=10",
        "description": "GET /api/customers"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Get orders list",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders?page=1&limit=10",
        "description": "GET /api/orders"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Create customer",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', String(j.id));",
              "if (j.addresses && j.addresses.length && j.addresses[0].id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('addressId', String(j.addresses[0].id));",
              "} else {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('addressId', '');",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Postman\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Customer\",\n  \"email\": \"customer.{{$guid}}@example.test\",\n  \"phone\": \"9800000000\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"internalNotes\": \"from postman collection\",\n  \"addresses\": [\n    {\n      \"street\": \"1 Collection Street\",\n      \"city\": \"Chennai\",\n      \"zipCode\": \"600001\",\n      \"isPrimary\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/customers",
        "description": "POST /api/customers — saves `customerId` and `addressId` for later requests."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6A. Batch create addresses (POST /api/addresses)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "if (j.addresses && j.addresses.length > 0 && j.addresses[0].id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('addressId', String(j.addresses[0].id));",
              "}",
              "if (j.addresses && j.addresses.length > 1 && j.addresses[1].id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('addressId2', String(j.addresses[1].id));",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": {{customerId}},\n  \"addresses\": [\n    {\n      \"line1\": \"Batch Street One\",\n      \"city\": \"Chennai\",\n      \"zipCode\": \"600003\",\n      \"buildingName\": \"Block A\",\n      \"isPrimary\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"line1\": \"Batch Street Two\",\n      \"city\": \"Chennai\",\n      \"zipCode\": \"600004\",\n      \"isPrimary\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/addresses",
        "description": "POST /api/addresses — batch create; refreshes `addressId` / `addressId2` from response."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6B. Batch update addresses (PUT /api/addresses)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.expect(j.addresses).to.be.an('array');"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"addresses\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": {{addressId}},\n      \"zipCode\": \"600099\",\n      \"buildingName\": \"Updated Block\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": {{addressId2}},\n      \"city\": \"Chennai\",\n      \"area\": \"Velachery\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/addresses",
        "description": "PUT /api/addresses — each item must include `id` (use 6A variables; run 6 before 6A)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6C. Update one address (PUT /api/addresses/:id)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"zipCode\": \"600100\",\n  \"phoneNo\": \"9800000001\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/addresses/{{addressId}}",
        "description": "PUT /api/addresses/{address_id} — single-row partial update (admin REST)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Create order",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "var j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('orderId', String(j.id));"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"customerId\": {{customerId}},\n  \"totalAmount\": 99.5,\n  \"address\": \"1 Collection Street\",\n  \"customerNotes\": \"postman roundtrip\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders",
        "description": "POST /api/orders — no bookingItems (avoids services catalog dependency). Saves `orderId`."
      }
    },
